==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carromata
<hw>Car`ro*ma"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. in Phil.
I.]</ety> <def>In the Philippines, a light, two-wheeled, boxlike vehicle
usually drawn by a single native pony and used to convey passengers
within city limits or for traveling. It is the common public
carriage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

